<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="perfect-adj">perfect <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'pɜːfɪkt/    美 /'pɜːrfɪkt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1">1.★ <strong>完美的；极好的</strong></h4>
<p>反 imperfect： </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He speaks perfect English. 
他讲一口地道的英语。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The car is in perfect condition. 
车况极佳。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— What do you think of the house?
这个房子怎么样？</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>— Perfect! It’s everything we’ve been looking for.
好极了！一切都是我们想要的。</p><footer>2013 辽宁改</footer></div>

<h4 id="2">2.★ <strong>最适当的；理想的：</strong></h4>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>The weather was <strong>perfect for</strong> the outdoor performance.
天气很适合户外活动。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>She is <strong>perfect for</strong> the job. 
她做那项工作再合适不过了。</p></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>perfection /pə'fekʃn/ n [U]   </p></div>